    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": "Is an MRI Leg painful?",
        "answer": "No. You only need to lie still; there is no pain or injection unless contrast is used."
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I eat before the scan?",
        "answer": "Yes, for a non-contrast MRI Leg. Fast 4 hours if contrast is planned.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "How soon can I get results?",
        "answer": "Reports are available within 24 hours at Cadabams Diagnostics.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Is the scan safe for kids?",
        "answer": "Absolutely. MRI uses no radiation, making it safe for children.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "What if I’m claustrophobic?",
        "answer": "We offer open-bore MRI machines and mild sedation options.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Are there any side effects or after-effects from a Leg MRI?",
        "answer": "The **Leg MRI** scan itself, using magnetic fields and radio waves, has no known persistent side effects. Most people can resume their normal activities immediately after the scan. If a contrast dye was used for your **Leg MRI**, there is a small risk of an allergic reaction (usually mild, like a rash or nausea, but rarely more serious). If you received sedation for claustrophobia or inability to lie still, you might feel groggy for a few hours and will need someone to drive you home. Otherwise, there are generally no after-effects from the **leg MRI scan procedure**."
      }
    ],
